\b \cf0 CheckSum Option
\b0 \
\
The user may select the type of message digest to be generated for a file during Single File or Batch Files processing. Apple\'92s software updates usually uses SHA1 (Secure Hash Algorithm).\
\
\

\b Concurrency Option
\b0 \
\
The slider is used to set the number of tasks that can run concurrently during batch files processing. An instance of NSOperation will be instantiated for each file whose message digest is to be generated. \
A value of 1 means the tasks will be executed consecutively one task at a time. A value of 4 means up to 4 tasks may be performed at any one time.\
The user can choose a value that is optimal for his/her system with no blocking of the main UI queue. If the selected value is too high, a multicoloured beach may be displayed. The default value is 4.  The maximum value is 32. There are a total of 8 intervals which means each tick mark represents a multiple of 4. A value of 0 means the default value 4.\
\
